                            <h2 class="display-6 fw-bold text-primary mb-4">
                                <i class="fas fa-bullseye me-2"></i>Our Mission
                            </h2>
                            <p class="lead">To systematically promote a culture of peace, active tolerance, and patriotic responsibility among all Ugandans through strategic advocacy, inclusive cross-party dialogue, grassroots mobilization, and citizen-led national preservation campaigns.</p>
                            <p>Friends of Uganda (FoU) is a transformative, citizen-driven national initiative designed to transcend political divisions and foster sustainable peace, unity, and national preservation during Uganda's 2026 electoral cycle and beyond.</p>
                            <p>Our core philosophy asserts that while political opinions legitimately differ, our shared Ugandan identity and collective responsibility to safeguard our nation's resources, institutions, and social fabric are paramount and permanentâ€”transcending any electoral season or political actor. Uganda, sovereign since 1962, will outlive all political cycles.</p>
                            <p>We mobilize citizens from all walks of life to become active "friends" of their country, promoting reconciliation, rejecting divisive rhetoric, and building a cohesive society through grassroots action, strategic communication, and nationwide institutional presence.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

